@Node "Features" "sig.guide/Features"
@Next "Distribution"
@Prev "Introduction"
@Toc "Main"

Features
********

   @{b}SIRDS_GEN@{ub} V3.7 takes a picture or a formula as input. When using a
picture, the value of the pixels determine the depth-position of the
@{i}SIRDS@{ui} there. e.g. if you have a 32-color picture, then you have a
maximum of 32 @{i}layers@{ui} in the picture, where the background is the lowest
area, and the pixels with number 31 will be the highest one. But if you
prefer using a grayscale, then you can sort the colors first, to let
the darkest color describe the lowest area, and the lightest one the
highest.

   The second input form is a mathematical function.

   The output is either a @{i}SIRDS@{ui} or a SIS, when you supply a pattern.

   Here is a further list of options:
   @{b}*@{ub} function plotting, and viewing as @{i}SIRDS@{ui}

   @{b}*@{ub} free choice of screen-mode

   @{b}*@{ub} scaling of the picture

   @{b}*@{ub} should run on Gfx-cards too (not much tested, but Picasso II is
     working)

   @{b}*@{ub} automatic correction of the eyewidth to the displaymode

   @{b}*@{ub} uses datatypes for reading the picture

   @{b}*@{ub} 32-bit color-funktions are used.

   @{b}*@{ub} uses a symmetric algorithm

   @{b}*@{ub} generation of SIS possible

   @{b}*@{ub} flimmering

   @{b}*@{ub} various Settings possible

   @{b}*@{ub} 4 different pattern-modes


@EndNode

@Node "Requirements" "sig.guide/Requirements"
@Next "Installation"
@Prev "Distribution"
@Toc "Main"

Requirements
************

   @{b}SIRDS_GEN@{ub} V3.7 requires Kickstart 2.0+ & Workbench V2.0+, though
some function work only with Kickstart 3.0+.

   An accelerator with FPU is nice, but not recommended (use the
68000er version if you haven't got one).

   Here is a list of functions disabled when operating under Kickstart
2.0:

   @{b}*@{ub} If you only have Workbench 2.0 you can't change the screenmode in
     the Prefs-window, and no localization is possible. Only possible
     with Workbench V2.1+

   @{b}*@{ub} The picture to be converted can't be viewed before

   @{b}*@{ub} The preview-Window of the Prefs-window is disabled

   @{b}*@{ub} only loading of IFF-ILBM pictures possible


@EndNode

@Node "Usage" "sig.guide/Usage"
@Next "Keys-Menus"
@Prev "Registration"
@Toc "Main"

Usage
*****

   Choose the right version: If you own a computer with at least a
68020 AND a 68881 then you can use the normal version. Otherwise you
have to use the 68000-version.

   After starting you are prompted with the @{"Preferences window" Link "Preferences window"} to do
the various settings there. Either enter a formula, or (after
finishing) you are prompted for a picture to load. Now the picture will
be loaded into a screen (the PIC-Screen). Another Screen (the
SIRDS-Screen) will be opened, and the @{i}SIRDS@{ui} will be calculated.

   Due to the fact, that the same loop, for both screens (PIC & SIRDS)
is used you have the same menus, and keyboard functions. So saving for
example effects the current active window.


@EndNode

